ENTRY       EC 2.3.1.220                Enzyme
NAME        2,4,6-trihydroxybenzophenone synthase;
            benzophenone synthase (ambiguous);
            BPS (ambiguous)
CLASS       Transferases;
            Acyltransferases;
            Transferring groups other than aminoacyl groups
SYSNAME     malonyl-CoA:benzoyl-CoA malonyltransferase (2,4,6-trihydroxybenzophenone-forming)
REACTION    3 malonyl-CoA + benzoyl-CoA = 4 CoA + 2,4,6-trihydroxybenzophenone + 3 CO2 [RN:R02447]
ALL_REAC    R02447
SUBSTRATE   malonyl-CoA [CPD:C00083];
            benzoyl-CoA [CPD:C00512]
PRODUCT     CoA [CPD:C00010];
            2,4,6-trihydroxybenzophenone [CPD:C06356];
            CO2 [CPD:C00011]
COMMENT     Involved in the biosynthesis of plant xanthones. The enzyme from the plant Hypericum androsaemum L can use 3-hydroxybenzoyl-CoA instead of benzoyl-CoA, but with lower activity (cf. EC 2.3.1.151, 2,3',4,6-tetrahydroxybenzophenone synthase).
